#X text 51 150 For the gain factor \, we're actually modulating the amplitudes of each oscillator by a multichannel low frequency noise (random ramps at the rate of 1 Hz)., f 53;
#X text 51 73 In this example we have a knob to set an overall detuning factor \, multiplied by random values within the -1 to 1 range. The new idea is to set the gain of each oscillator and have them spaced in the stereo field., f 53;
#X text 51 200 The [spread.mc~] object takes a multichannel input and evenly spreads it into a given number of channels (which is 2 in here and means an even distribution in the stereo field)., f 53;
